An agreement has been reached, thanks to President Biden's leadership, to release dozens of hostages who were taken by Hamas in acts of terrorism. President Biden and Vice President Harris express their prayers for the well-being of the hostages and gratitude for their upcoming reunions. Israel has committed to supporting an extended pause to ensure the deal's full implementation and provide humanitarian aid to Gaza civilians. The flow of aid needs to increase significantly, and civilians must be protected. The release of all remaining hostages by Hamas is also called for. President Biden and Vice President Harris prioritize the safety of Americans, and they welcome the agreement as it means some Americans will be coming home. They assure families of hostages that they are not alone and that their commitment to these Americans remains unwavering.